From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tim2tox-bootstrap <bootstrap@local>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 22:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 14/14] instance-tagged listener routing for singleton managers

Three manager singletons in the vendored SDK
(`TIMMessageManager` / `TIMConversationManager` / `TIMFriendshipManager`)
hold a single flat listener list each. Patches 0008 / 0011 / 0013
intentionally fall through to those singleton lists for non-zero
`instance_id` so callbacks delivered from the multi-instance Tim2Tox
path still reach listeners registered via the binary-replacement API
surface. That works fine for production toxee (always instance_id 0),
but in tim2tox auto_tests (`scenario_message`, `scenario_events`,
`scenario_file*`, etc.) multiple simulated peers register listeners
against the SAME flat list ŌĆö so an event meant for Bob fires Alice's
listener too, and tests that wait on a completer from the wrong node
complete on the wrong event.

This patch adds an opt-in per-instance routing layer:

1. `NativeLibraryManager` gains two static fields:
   - `currentRegistrationInstanceId` ŌĆö set by the tim2tox layer
     (`Tim2ToxInstance.runWithInstance`) right before invoking
     `TIMxxxManager.instance.addXxxListener(...)`; tags the listener
     with the instance id in a per-instance bucket on the manager.
   - `currentDispatchInstanceId` ŌĆö set by `_handleGlobalCallback`
     for the duration of listener fan-out; tells managers which
     bucket to dispatch to.

2. `_handleGlobalCallback` is split: the preamble + dispatch-context
   wrapping live in `_handleGlobalCallback`, the per-callback switch
   moves to `_dispatchGlobalCallback`. The wrap is a try/finally so
   the previous dispatch id is restored on exceptions.

3. Each of the three managers gets:
   - `_instanceListeners: Map<int, List<...>>` ŌĆö per-instance buckets
   - `add*Listener` ALSO appends to the bucket keyed by
     `currentRegistrationInstanceId` (when set and non-zero)
   - `remove*Listener` purges from BOTH the flat list and any buckets
   - `_listenersForCurrentDispatch()` ŌĆö returns the per-instance
     bucket for `currentDispatchInstanceId` when present and
     non-empty, ELSE the flat list (the fallback preserves byte
     identical behavior for single-instance toxee)
   - `listenersForInstance(int?)` ŌĆö public counterpart so
     `Tim2ToxSdkPlatform._notifyXxxListeners` can filter its own
     singleton fan-out the same way

4. The 12 `for (var listener in v2TimAdvancedMsgListenerList)` sites
   in `_internalInitMessageListener` (and the equivalent 13 / 15 sites
   in the conversation / friendship managers) all switch to
   `_listenersForCurrentDispatch()`.

Hard invariant: when `currentRegistrationInstanceId` is null or 0
(production toxee), neither bucket nor dispatch routing fires ŌĆö
`_listenersForCurrentDispatch()` and `listenersForInstance(null|0)`
both fall back to the existing flat list. This is byte-identical to
pre-0014 behavior; the only cost is two static null reads per
dispatch and an unconditional null/zero check per add/remove.

Companion tim2tox-side changes (NOT in this SDK patch ŌĆö they live in
the tim2tox submodule):
  - `dart/lib/instance/tim2tox_instance.dart`: `runWithInstance` /
    `runWithInstanceAsync` stamp `currentRegistrationInstanceId` while
    `setCurrentInstance(handle)` is in effect.
  - `dart/lib/sdk/tim2tox_sdk_platform.dart`: `_notifyAdvancedMsg /
    Conversation / FriendshipListeners` accept an optional
    `dispatchInstanceId` and route the singleton fan-out through
    `listenersForInstance(dispatchInstanceId)` so download/upload
    progress for instance B does not fire instance A's listener.
